In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump acknowledges the challenges posed by HIV/AIDS and the progress made in combating the disease. He highlights that an HIV/AIDS diagnosis is no longer a death sentence thanks to lifesaving medications. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of connecting those affected by HIV/AIDS with high-quality healthcare and eliminating the stigma surrounding the disease. The President reiterates the commitment to achieving the goals set out in the National HIV/AIDS Strategy and mentions the Ryan White HIV/AIDS Program as a critical component of the domestic public health response. The proclamation also emphasizes collaboration with national and international stakeholders through the U.S. President's Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR) and acknowledges the progress made in saving lives and preventing HIV transmission. The President calls for appropriate activities on World AIDS Day to remember those who have lost their lives to AIDS and show support and compassion to those living with HIV.